# Pre-Battle Observations at the Circle of Thunder

## Scene summary (from gm-assist, verbatim)

#### The party arrives at the Circle of Thunder and observes a group of anchorites performing a mysterious summoning ritual, debating how to intervene.
- The party observes two half-orc spellcasters and numerous twig blight minions performing a ritual at the Circle of Thunder.
- Valphine identifies the activity as a summoning ritual through a successful religion check, while Soma and Vukradin roll poorly on their own checks.
- The party debates whether to cast Silence to interrupt the ritual, but discovers the ritual has no vocal component — the anchorites are dancing.
- Initiative is rolled as the party prepares to engage the anchorites and twig blights.

## Verbatim moments

There are no moments in this transcript that match the described scene. The transcript contains a D&D session set in Daggerford, Beregost, and Candlekeep involving characters named Thorin, Daz, Zaltir, and Grigam — it contains no Circle of Thunder, no anchorites, no twig blights, no summoning ritual, no Valphine, no Soma, and no Vukradin. Silence would be correct here rather than fabrication.
